## Scenario 4: Error Handling - {{ERROR_SCENARIO_NAME}}

```gherkin
  Scenario: {{ERROR_SCENARIO_NAME}}
    Given {{GIVEN_ERROR}}
    When {{WHEN_ERROR}}
    Then {{THEN_ERROR}}
    And the system should display error message "{{ERROR_MESSAGE}}"
    And the error code should be {{ERROR_CODE}}
    And {{THEN_ERROR_RECOVERY}}
```

**Error Recovery:**
{{ERROR_RECOVERY}}

**Validation Points:**
- [ ] Error message is user-friendly
- [ ] Error is logged with proper context
- [ ] System state remains consistent
- [ ] {{CUSTOM_ERROR_VALIDATION}}

---

## Scenario 5: Boundary Conditions

```gherkin
  Scenario Outline: {{BOUNDARY_NAME}}
    Given {{GIVEN_BOUNDARY}}
    When I {{WHEN_BOUNDARY}} with <input_value>
    Then {{THEN_BOUNDARY}} <expected_result>

    Examples:
      | input_value | expected_result | notes |
      | {{VALUE_1}} | {{RESULT_1}} | {{NOTES_1}} |
      | {{VALUE_2}} | {{RESULT_2}} | {{NOTES_2}} |
      | {{VALUE_3}} | {{RESULT_3}} | {{NOTES_3}} |
      | {{VALUE_4}} | {{RESULT_4}} | {{NOTES_4}} |
```

**Test Cases:**
- Minimum valid value
- Maximum valid value
- Just below minimum (invalid)
- Just above maximum (invalid)
- Empty/null value
- Special characters

---

## Scenario 6: Performance Requirements

```gherkin
  Scenario: {{PERF_SCENARIO_NAME}}
    Given {{GIVEN_PERF}}
    When {{WHEN_PERF}}
    Then the response time should be less than {{RESPONSE_TIME}}ms
    And the operation should complete within {{TIMEOUT}}seconds
    And system resources should remain under {{RESOURCE_LIMIT}}
```

**Performance Criteria:**
- Response time: < {{RESPONSE_TIME}}ms (95th percentile)
- Throughput: {{THROUGHPUT}} requests/second
- Concurrent users: {{CONCURRENT_USERS}}
- Resource usage: < {{CPU_LIMIT}}% CPU, < {{MEMORY_LIMIT}}GB RAM

---

## Scenario 7: Security Requirements

```gherkin
  Scenario: {{SECURITY_SCENARIO_NAME}}
    Given {{GIVEN_SECURITY}}
    And the user has {{PERMISSION}} permission
    When {{WHEN_SECURITY}}
    Then {{THEN_SECURITY}}
    And the action should be logged to audit trail
    And sensitive data should be {{SECURITY_ACTION}}
```

**Security Checklist:**
- [ ] Authentication verified
- [ ] Authorization checked
- [ ] Input validation performed
- [ ] Output sanitization applied
- [ ] Audit logging enabled
- [ ] Sensitive data protected
- [ ] {{CUSTOM_SECURITY_CHECK}}

---

## Scenario 8: Integration Points

```gherkin
  Scenario: {{INTEGRATION_SCENARIO}}
    Given {{GIVEN_INTEGRATION}}
    And the external system {{EXTERNAL_SYSTEM}} is available
    When {{WHEN_INTEGRATION}}
    Then the system should send request to {{EXTERNAL_SYSTEM}}
    And the system should receive response within {{INTEGRATION_TIMEOUT}}ms
    And {{THEN_INTEGRATION}}
```

**Integration Requirements:**
- External system: {{EXTERNAL_SYSTEM}}
- Protocol: {{PROTOCOL}}
- Timeout: {{INTEGRATION_TIMEOUT}}ms
- Retry logic: {{RETRY_LOGIC}}
- Fallback behavior: {{FALLBACK}}

---

## Scenario 9: Data Validation

```gherkin
  Scenario Outline: Data Validation for {{FIELD_NAME}}
    Given a user is on the {{PAGE_NAME}} page
    When they enter <input> in the {{FIELD_NAME}} field
    Then the validation should <result>
    And the error message should be <message>

    Examples:
      | input | result | message |
      | {{VALID_INPUT}} | accept | null |
      | {{INVALID_INPUT_1}} | reject | "{{ERROR_MSG_1}}" |
      | {{INVALID_INPUT_2}} | reject | "{{ERROR_MSG_2}}" |
      | {{INVALID_INPUT_3}} | reject | "{{ERROR_MSG_3}}" |
```

**Validation Rules:**
- Format: {{FORMAT_RULE}}
- Length: {{LENGTH_RULE}}
- Pattern: {{PATTERN_RULE}}
- Allowed values: {{ALLOWED_VALUES}}
- Forbidden values: {{FORBIDDEN_VALUES}}

---

## Scenario 10: Accessibility Requirements

```gherkin
  Scenario: {{ACCESSIBILITY_SCENARIO}}
    Given a user with {{ACCESSIBILITY_NEED}}
    When they {{WHEN_ACCESSIBILITY}}
    Then {{THEN_ACCESSIBILITY}}
    And the feature should be {{ACCESSIBILITY_STANDARD}} compliant
    And screen readers should announce "{{SCREEN_READER_TEXT}}"
```

**Accessibility Checklist:**
- [ ] WCAG {{WCAG_LEVEL}} compliant
- [ ] Keyboard navigation supported
- [ ] Screen reader compatible
- [ ] Sufficient color contrast ({{CONTRAST_RATIO}}:1)
- [ ] Focus indicators visible
- [ ] ARIA labels present
- [ ] {{CUSTOM_ACCESSIBILITY}}

---

## Negative Test Scenarios

### Scenario 11: Unauthorized Access
```gherkin
  Scenario: Unauthorized user attempts to {{ACTION}}
    Given a user without {{REQUIRED_PERMISSION}} permission
    When they attempt to {{ACTION}}
    Then the system should deny access
    And display "Access Denied" message
    And redirect to {{REDIRECT_PAGE}}
    And log the unauthorized attempt
```

### Scenario 12: Invalid State
```gherkin
  Scenario: Action attempted in invalid state
    Given the system is in {{INVALID_STATE}} state
    When the user attempts to {{ACTION}}
    Then the system should prevent the action
    And display message "{{STATE_ERROR_MESSAGE}}"
    And {{STATE_RECOVERY_ACTION}}
```

---

## Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria

### Usability
- [ ] UI is intuitive for {{TARGET_USER}} users
- [ ] {{KEY_ACTION}} can be completed in < {{MAX_STEPS}} steps
- [ ] Help text/tooltips available for complex fields
- [ ] {{CUSTOM_USABILITY}}

### Compatibility
- [ ] Works on Chrome {{CHROME_VERSION}}+
- [ ] Works on Firefox {{FIREFOX_VERSION}}+
- [ ] Works on Safari {{SAFARI_VERSION}}+
- [ ] Works on Edge {{EDGE_VERSION}}+
- [ ] Mobile responsive (iOS {{IOS_VERSION}}+, Android {{ANDROID_VERSION}}+)

### Maintainability
- [ ] Code follows {{CODING_STANDARD}} standards
- [ ] Unit test coverage > {{COVERAGE_THRESHOLD}}%
- [ ] API documentation generated
- [ ] Logging implemented with appropriate levels

---

## Definition of Done

- [ ] All scenarios pass
- [ ] Code reviewed and approved
- [ ] Unit tests written and passing ({{COVERAGE_THRESHOLD}}% coverage)
- [ ] Integration tests passing
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Security scan completed (no high/critical issues)
- [ ] Performance tests meet criteria
- [ ] Accessibility audit passed
- [ ] Product Owner approval obtained
- [ ] Deployed to {{ENVIRONMENT}} environment
- [ ] {{CUSTOM_DOD_1}}
- [ ] {{CUSTOM_DOD_2}}

